- 2:08pm The Heart of Mexico Literary and Visual Storytelling Project takes students from both UNT and the Autonomous University of the State of Mexico to small towns in Mexico, to create multimedia stories in teams and receive cultural immersion.     Author of "The Perfect Storm" among keynote speakers at 2017 Mayborn Literary Nonfiction Conference 03/07/2017 - 1:52pm The July 21-23 conference, with a theme of "The Power of Words," has a new, lower registration fee for UNT students. Wayne Miller named 2017 UNT Rilke Prize winner 03/07/2017 - 12:30pm Wayne Miller is the 2017 UNT Rilke Prize winner for his book of poetry, “Post-.” The $10,000 prize, sponsored by UNT’s Department of English, recognizes a book published by a mid-career poet that demonstrates exceptional artistry and vision. UNT to host Women’s History Month speaker on March 23 03/06/2017 - 12:01pm Katie Hindmarch-Watson, assistant professor at Johns Hopkins University and cultural historian of the British Empire, will discuss queer mediators’ foundational role in early radio broadcasting of the BBC during a free lecture at the University of North Texas March 23. UNT named Osher Lifelong Learning Institute 02/27/2017 - 10:08am The University of North Texas has been named an Osher Lifelong Learning Institute—a recognition by The Bernard Osher Foundation of efforts at the university’s Emeritus College to serve the 50 and over population. Award-winning authors headed to UNT for spring Visiting Writers Series 02/21/2017 - 9:28am Three writers will be appearing at the University of North Texas for the spring 2017 Visiting Writers Series sponsored by UNT’s Creative Writing Program. UNT student awarded $25,000 grant from the National Endowment for the Arts 02/20/2017 - 10:02am University of North Texas student Matt Morton has been awarded a $25,000 grant from the National Endowment for the Arts Literature Fellowship program. UNT guest speaker to discuss antisemitism of the left and right political spectrum 02/